# Lively HTML Rendering System — Implementation Plan

## 1. Spec Comparison

### Where the Specs Agree (Confirmed Approach)
Both specifications converge on the same core architecture:

| Concept | Agreement |
|---|---|
| **Separation of concerns** | Content generation, layout, behaviour, and QC are four distinct responsibilities |
| **Pipeline stages** | Content → LayoutPlan → BehaviorPlan → ResponsivePlan → HTML → universal.js → runtime.js → QC |
| **universal.js** | Safety net that runs first, unconditionally, on every page — nav anchors, reading progress, table overflow scroll, diagram zoom detection, keyboard navigation |
| **runtime.js** | Reads `data-behaviour` attributes, activates named interactions, shared across all templates |
| **Behaviour vocabulary** | A shared registry of named behaviours (hint-toggle, step-reveal, accordion, zoom, sticky-sidebar, section-tabs, scrollspy, etc.) |
| **LLM never writes JS** | LLM emits HTML + `data-behaviour` attributes only |
| **Three plans** | LayoutPlan, BehaviorPlan, ResponsivePlan are structured objects produced before HTML |
| **Template capability declaration** | JSON schema declaring allowed behaviours, preferred defaults, interaction ceiling, responsive fallbacks |
| **Three confidence tiers** | Tier 1 = automatic/deterministic, Tier 2 = LLM-reasoned, Tier 3 = safe fallback |
| **Visual QC at three widths** | Desktop, tablet, mobile — catches layout, structural, visual, and behaviour problems |
| **Section-level rerender** | Failed blocks are regenerated individually, not whole sections |
| **Print fallback** | All hidden content visible when printed |

### Where They Differ (Resolutions)

| Topic | Claude spec (FINAL_RENDERING_SPEC) | ChatGPT spec (adaptive_html_rendering) | Resolution |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Behaviour categories** | 6 tiers: Disclosure, Visual, Navigation, Assessment, Subject, Premium | 4 tiers: Disclosure, Visual, Navigation, Assessment | **Take Claude's 6-tier system** — more complete and specific |
| **Layout decision rules** | Detailed table with override conditions (insight-strip > 2 lines → comparison-grid, etc.) | Not specified | **Take Claude's override table** — concrete and implementable |
| **QC issue report format** | Structured: location, problem, severity, fix, confidence, action | Mentioned but not specified | **Take Claude's format** as the schema |
| **Two display modes** | Long scroll + section tabs, teacher-selected | Not mentioned | **Take Claude's** — adds value, straightforward |
| **Classroom display (>1400px)** | Breakpoint increase for projectors | Not mentioned | **Take Claude's** — adds a fourth CSS breakpoint, easy to add |
| **Plans as HTML comments** | Plans recorded as HTML comment at top | Plans recorded but format unclear | **HTML comments** — inspectable, machine-parseable |
| **Behaviour safety** | Unknown behaviours logged, page falls back to static | Claude also mentions unknown behaviours gracefully degrade | Both agree; Claude is more specific — **follow Claude: log + static fallback** |
| **Three breakpoints** | Desktop >900px, Tablet 600-900px, Mobile <600px | Desktop, Tablet, Mobile (no specific values) | **Use Claude's px values** |
| **Keyboard navigation** | Arrow keys between sections | Arrow keys mentioned | **Follow Claude** — sections + tabs navigation |

### Unique Contributions Taken From Each

**From ChatGPT spec only:**
- Behaviour categories concept (even though Claude also mentions categories, ChatGPT structures them cleanly)
- Explicit phasing guidance (Phase 1–4)
- `quiz-check` and `toggle-view` in assessment category
- Concept of "interaction must improve understanding" as a design principle

**From Claude spec only:**
- `expand-card`, `compare-toggle`, `equation-reveal`, `tree-stepper`, `timeline-scrubber`, `graph-slider`, `pyodide-cell`, `simulation` behaviours
- Specific layout decision override table
- `self-check` behaviour
- Two display modes (long scroll vs section tabs)
- Classroom display breakpoint
- `data-term` and `data-definition` attributes on vocabulary terms
- `data-zoom="true"` explicit attribute

