### Component 4: Plan Generation (LayoutPlan, BehaviorPlan, ResponsivePlan)

#### [NEW] [plan_generator.py](file:///c:/Projects/Textbook%20agent/backend/src/textbook_agent/domain/services/plan_generator.py)

A deterministic plan generator that produces plans without an LLM call (consistent with "Renderer has no LLM calls" invariant). Uses rules from both specs:

- `generate_layout_plan(sections, template) -> LayoutPlan`: applies the layout decision override table (Claude spec §Layout Decision Rules)
- `generate_behavior_plan(sections, template) -> BehaviorPlan`: applies Tier 1 automatics, respects template capability ceiling
- `generate_responsive_plan(template) -> ResponsivePlan`: builds from template's responsive_fallbacks + standard breakpoints

The plans are recorded as structured objects on the [PresentationManifest](file:///c:/Projects/Textbook%20agent/backend/src/textbook_agent/domain/entities/presentation.py#165-179). The plans are also serialised as HTML comments in the output.

#### [MODIFY] [presentation_engine.py](file:///c:/Projects/Textbook%20agent/backend/src/textbook_agent/infrastructure/renderer/presentation_engine.py)

- `PresentationAdapter.build_manifest()` calls the plan generator and attaches plans to the manifest
- Plans drive `data-behaviour` attribute emission on blocks
- `PresentationEngine.render()` injects plan HTML comments at the top of the rendered output

