### Component 6: runtime.js — The Behaviour Engine

#### [NEW] [runtime.js](file:///c:/Projects/Textbook%20agent/backend/src/textbook_agent/infrastructure/renderer/assets/runtime.js)

Reads `data-behaviour` attributes after universal.js has run. Implements a dispatcher pattern:

```js
const BEHAVIOURS = {
  'hint-toggle': initHintToggle,
  'step-reveal': initStepReveal,
  'accordion': initAccordion,
  'zoom': initZoom,
  'sticky-sidebar': initStickySidebar,
  'section-tabs': initSectionTabs,
  'scrollspy': initScrollspy,
  'expand-card': initExpandCard,
  'highlight-row': initHighlightRow,
  'tooltip': initTooltip,
  'compare-toggle': initCompareToggle,
  'quiz-check': initQuizCheck,
  'self-check': initSelfCheck,
  'toggle-view': initToggleView,
};
```

Each behaviour handler:
- Receives the element with the `data-behaviour` attribute
- Attaches event listeners, creates UI controls
- Has a print fallback (CSS `@media print` shows all hidden content)
- Falls back gracefully if behaviour is unknown (logs to console, element remains static)

~400–500 lines of vanilla JS. No dependencies.

#### [NEW] [runtime.css](file:///c:/Projects/Textbook%20agent/backend/src/textbook_agent/infrastructure/renderer/assets/runtime.css)

Styles for all runtime behaviours: accordion arrows, step-reveal buttons, zoom overlay, sticky sidebar, tab bars, scrollspy active states, tooltip positioning. Includes comprehensive `@media print` rules.

