### Component 9: Updated LLM Prompt

#### [MODIFY] [formatting_rules.py](file:///c:/Projects/Textbook%20agent/backend/src/textbook_agent/domain/prompts/formatting_rules.py)

Add new prompt blocks teaching the LLM:
- `[PROMPT:LAYOUT_FIT]` — reason about content density before choosing components (the override table)
- `[PROMPT:BEHAVIOUR_ATTRIBUTES]` — emit `data-behaviour` attributes, never write JS or inline event handlers
- `[PROMPT:VOCABULARY_TERMS]` — mark first-use terms with `data-term` and `data-definition`
- `[PROMPT:PLAN_COMMENTS]` — emit LayoutPlan, BehaviorPlan, ResponsivePlan as HTML comments
- `[PROMPT:BEHAVIOUR_RULES]` — list the full behaviour vocabulary with categories, when to use each
- `[PROMPT:NEVER_RULES]` — never write JS, never invent behaviour names, never exceed template ceiling

> [!NOTE]
> Because the current system generates content as structured JSON (not raw HTML), the LLM prompt changes primarily affect the content structure. The `data-behaviour` attributes are added by the template engine based on the plans, not by the LLM directly. The prompt teaches the LLM to reason about layout fit so it structures content appropriately (e.g. splitting long comparisons into items rather than prose).

